Package: tseLCA
Type: Package
Title: Three-Step Estimation for Latent Class Analysis
Version: 0.1.3
Authors@R: person("Sam", "Lee", email = "samlee@arizona.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements BCH and ML three-step estimators for latent class
    analysis (LCA) with covariates and distal outcomes, following Bakk, Tekle &
    Vermunt (2013), Bakk & Kuha (2018), and Bakk, Lyrvall et al. (2025). The
    package uses multilevLCA for Step-1 measurement model estimation and
    provides correct sandwich variance estimation that propagates measurement
    uncertainty from the first-step LCA through classification-error correction
    in the final step. Supports polytomous items, missing data via FIML, and
    Gaussian, Poisson, and binomial distal outcome families. A data-generating
    process replicating the Bakk & Kuha (2018) simulation study is included.
